been borne out in explicit comparisons of protein simulations with different force fields, concentrating on structure details (Roterman et al., 1989; Ceccarelli and Marchi, 1997) or on fluctuation behavior (Teeter and Case, 1990; Price and Brooks, 2002). These results are often highly dependent on the strongly repulsive portions of the force field, which tend to be quite similar in different parameterizations, especially when

