Such a scheme leads to what have been called ‘‘perfect’’ radii (Onufriev et al., 2002). These, in conjunction with the functional form for the cross terms, equation 26, then yields very accurate cross terms when compared with numerical solutions of the Poisson equation. Thus the key to accurate GB models is the estimation of the effective radii (Onufriev et al., 2002; Lee et al., 2002).

