71

In practice, of course, obtaining ‘‘perfect’’ radii requires an expensive

solution to the Poisson-Boltzmann equation, and a faster algorithm for

computing the R i values is needed for efficient molecular dynamics

simulations. In the classical electrostatics of a linearly polarizable medium

( Jackson, 1999), the work required to assemble a charge distribution can

be formulated either in terms of a product of the charge distribution with

the electric potential, as in equation 23 above, or in terms of the scalar

product of the electric field E and the electric displacement D:

